==Irish Gaelic==
===Proper noun===
'''Garda'''
# the police force of the Republic of Ireland.
# the title of a male officer of that force. Female officers are correctly titled ''Ban Garda''.
#:''Garda Michael Egan and Ban Garda Niamh Murphy''

===Etymology===
Short form of Irish ''Garda Síochána na hÉireann'', meaning ''Guardians of the Peace of Ireland''

==Italian==
===Proper noun===
'''Garda'''
